# CJXplorer — Project Context

## What is this project?

CJXplorer is an agent-based service for researching and evaluating Customer Journeys (CJ) using a criteria-based evaluation model created by CX BP team.

Currently CJ analysis is done manually — it's expensive and doesn't cover the full scope of journeys. This service automates the process.

## Key User Stories

1. User uploads CJ screenshots → agent evaluates via criteria model
2. User specifies CJ + target apps/sites → agent autonomously navigates and evaluates (OpenClaw for mobile, Playwright for web)
3. User provides Pixso/Figma mockup screens (static, no prototypes) → agent evaluates CJ via criteria model

## Target Users

CX BP, product managers, UX researchers, designers, business analysts.

## Architecture Principles

- Modular: multiple loosely-coupled services/agents/tools that can be extended independently
- LLM-agnostic: services should not hard-depend on a specific model
- Simplicity-first stack
- Each module can use different LLMs/tools as appropriate

## Autonomous Navigation Stack

- Mobile (iOS/Android): OpenClaw (https://docs.openclaw.ai)
- Web: Playwright

## Current Phase

Architecture design — no implementation yet.

## Conventions

- Architecture docs go in `docs/architecture/`
- User story details go in `docs/user-stories/`
- Knowledge base (criteria model, heuristics) goes in `docs/knowledge-base/`
- All docs are in Russian unless specified otherwise
- Diagrams use Mermaid format where possible

## Deployment & Integration

- External perimeter: cloud/remote server — main logic, autonomous navigation, evaluation
- Internal perimeter (bank): mirrored agent logic on bank's internal LLM, works with mockups
- Bridge: file-based transfer between perimeters (reports go in, mockup analysis happens inside)
- Telegram bot as entry point (simplified output format)
- Web dashboard (full output format) — may exist in both perimeters
- History of evaluations stored long-term (screenshots, recordings, reports)

## Output Format

- Telegram: simplified report
- Dashboard/service: full interactive report
- Export: PDF, HTML, markdown

## Learning Loop

- Human verifies selected good/bad scenarios
- Cumulative verified base used for agent improvement (fine-tuning / few-shot)
- Long-term goal: autonomous agent that can CREATE customer journeys (not just evaluate)

## Competitor Analysis

- Agent researches multiple apps/sites in parallel for the same CJ
- Produces comparative evaluation across all targets

